content:
Not a museum — but interference.
A fragment of languages that shouldn’t have survived — but did.
And are still too temporary.

*******

This is the part of the internet where survival glitches. They’re flickering, held, never fixed.

*******

We're opening access to keep them lived.

Gupapuyŋu now.
Gàidhlig soon.
Then whoever speaks next.
